        <headline>Flood Warning issued April 7 at 11:04PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Texas...

Sabine River Near Gladewater affecting Smith, Wood, Upshur and
Gregg Counties.

Sabine River Near Hawkins affecting Smith, Wood and Upshur
Counties.

Sabine River Near Mineola affecting Smith and Wood Counties.

For the Sabine River...including Mineola, Hawkins, Gladewater,
Longview, Beckville, Logansport...Minor flooding is forecast.

* WHAT...Minor flooding is forecast.

* WHERE...Sabine River near Hawkins.

* WHEN...Until further notice.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 9:45 PM CDT Monday the stage was 22.6 feet.
- Bankfull stage is 22.0 feet.
- Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage
early tomorrow afternoon and continue rising to 27.8 feet
early Saturday afternoon. Additional rises are possible
thereafter.
- Flood stage is 23.0 feet.
- Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of
27.7 feet on 06/10/2016.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>

Do not drive cars through flooded areas.
Caution is urged when walking near riverbanks.
Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.

Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive
cars through flooded areas.

For more hydrologic information, copy and paste the following website
address into your favorite web browser URL bar:
https://water.noaa.gov/wfo/SHV

The next statement will be issued Tuesday evening at 1115 PM CDT.</instruction>
